Colombian Stocks: Coltejer, Canacol Energy, Ecopetrol Rise

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-04T21:43:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/colombian-stocks-canacol-energy-textiles-fabricato-increase.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.3 percent to 15,381.15, while the
Colcap Index increased 0.3 percent to 1,788.14.  Oil producers rose after crude surged to a 29-month high on
concern unrest in  Libya  will spread to other North African and
Middle East oil exporters, curbing shipments.    Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company , climbed 2.7 percent to 3,245 pesos, the highest level
since Nov. 9.    Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s largest oil company,
advanced 1.5 percent to 4,060 pesos, the highest price since
Dec. 30.    Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , a Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, gained 1.2 percent to 85 centavos. Colombia’s
Foreign Minister Maria Angela Holguin met with her counterpart
Nicolas Maduro in Caracas yesterday where they announced the two
countries signed 13 bilateral agreements including trade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  